    "caption": "Born ready, running before the sun is fully up.",
    "shortDescription": "Unlike baby rabbits, hares are born fully furred, eyes open, and ready to run within hours — a survival strategy on open land where there's nowhere to hide. Hares rely on pure speed, zigzagging at up to seventy kilometers per hour to shake off a chasing fox or hawk. Fun fact: Mountain hares change their coat from brown in summer to brilliant white in winter to match the snow."
